Xeroderma Pigmentosum (XP) is a rare genetic disorder that makes individuals extremely sensitive to ultraviolet (UV) light, leading to severe sunburn, eye problems, and a high risk of skin cancer. The Xeroderma Pigmentosum Treatment market can be segmented based on treatment type, end-user, and region. In terms of treatment type, the market includes medication, photoprotection strategies, gene therapy, and other emerging treatment options. Photoprotection involves lifestyle modifications and the use of sunscreens, sunglasses, and protective clothing to minimize UV exposure. Gene therapy is an innovative approach that aims to correct the genetic defects associated with XP. As for end-users, the market serves hospitals, clinics, and research institutes that cater to XP patients. Geographically, the market is divided into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa regions.

